-per-month-100531473.html?src=rss]]><source_id> engadget_479</source_id><guid ispermalink="false"> 812e6cef-84ce-4a92-91f2-1b8efbb6c9f6</guid><dc:creator>史蒂夫·登特</dc:creator><source/><![CDATA[Engadget]]><dc:publisher>恩杰特</dc:publisher><dc:rightsholder>恩杰特</dc:rightsholder><pubDate>Thu, 20 Jul 2023 10:05:31 +0000</pubDate><ingested> 1689843824</ingested><modified> 2023-07-20T09:03:48+00:00</modified><category><![CDATA[Social & Online Media]]></category><category><![CDATA[site|engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[provider_name|Engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[region|US]]></category><category><![CDATA[language|en-US]]></category><category><![CDATA[author_name|Steve Dent]]></category><media:content height="2362" medium="image" url="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2022-08/6650f7f0-14b2-11ed-ba7b-70623770e37e" width="3543"><media:keywords>标题</media:keywords><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[1]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[ ]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[ ]]></media:description><media:title><![CDATA[ ]]></media:title></media:content><media:content height="2362" medium="image" url="https://media-mbst-pub-ue1.s3.amazonaws.com/creatr-uploaded-images/2022-08/6650f7f0-14b2-11ed-ba7b-70623770e37e" width="3543"><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[2]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[NurPhoto via Getty Images]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[TV remote control is seen with YouTube Premium logo displayed on a screen in this illustration photo taken in Krakow, Poland on February 6, 2022. (Photo by Jakub Porzycki/NurPhoto via Getty Images)]]></media:description><media:title><![CDATA[Streaming Services Photo Illustrations]]></media:title></media:content></item><item><title><![CDATA[WhatsApp makes it easier to send messages to unsaved numbers]]></title><description type="html"><![CDATA[<p>在 WhatsApp 上向新朋友发送消息将变得更加简单。 <a data-i13n="cpos:1;pos:1" href="https://wabetainfo.com/whatsapp-for-ios-and-android-get-a-feature-to-quickly-open-chats-with-unknown-phone-numbers/">据<em>WABetaInfo</em>报道，</a>一项新的更新正在推出，让你可以联系任何你想要的人，而无需先保存他们的信息。没错，对于您<a data-i13n="cpos:2;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/whatsapps-new-channels-feature-lets-accounts-send-one-way-updates-to-followers-090843232.html">通过 WhatsApp 联系过</a>一次之后就不再联系的人，“Lisa 图书馆”或“South 4th Paul 公寓”不再保存任何联系人信息。</p><p>您可以像开始发送任何消息一样尝试此新功能。单击主屏幕上的新消息按钮（Apple 设备位于右上角，Android 设备位于右下角），然后在搜索栏中输入号码。该号码将显示在“不在您的通讯录中”类别下。该人的电话号码和个人资料照片的右侧是单击“聊天”的选项，这使您可以直接与他们进行对话。</p><span id="end-legacy-contents"></span><p>到目前为止，唯一的例外包括通过网络链接开始对话或在群聊中回复未保存的号码。但是，这仍然需要您通过<a data-i13n="cpos:3;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/whatsapp-feature-update-qr-code-contacts-152951474.html">二维码</a>或您已经认识的人的邀请进入聊天。 WhatsApp 的最新更新正在向所有用户推出，因此您应该很快就能使用新功能。</p>本文最初发表在 Engadget 上：https://www.engadget.com/whatsapp-makes-it-easier-to-send-messages-to-unsaved-numbers-093511724.html?src=rss]]>; </description><link/><![CDATA[https://www.engadget.com/whatsapp-makes-it-easier-to-send-messages-to-unsaved-numbers-093511724.html?src=rss]]><source_id> engadget_479</source_id><guid ispermalink="false"> 701e490e-3ac4-47b9-8095-70c8864a8f4a</guid><dc:creator>萨拉·菲尔丁</dc:creator><source/><![CDATA[Engadget]]><dc:publisher>恩杰特</dc:publisher><dc:rightsholder>恩杰特</dc:rightsholder><pubDate>Thu, 20 Jul 2023 09:35:11 +0000</pubDate><ingested> 1689847704</ingested><modified> 2023-07-20T10:08:26+00:00 </modified><category><![CDATA[site|engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[provider_name|Engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[region|US]]></category><category><![CDATA[language|en-US]]></category><category><![CDATA[author_name|Sarah Fielding]]></category><media:content height="534" medium="image" url="https://media.zenfs.com/en/reuters.com/03c084f4fcef33110f6d89320da04a26" width="800"><media:keywords>标题</media:keywords><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[1]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[ ]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[ ]]></media:description><media:title><![CDATA[ ]]></media:title></media:content><media:content height="534" medium="image" url="https://media.zenfs.com/en/reuters.com/03c084f4fcef33110f6d89320da04a26" width="800"><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[2]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[ ]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[ ]]></media:description><media:title><![CDATA[Meta introduces broadcast tool Channels on WhatsApp]]></media:title></media:content></item><item><title><![CDATA[Kevin Mitnick, formerly the world’s ‘most-wanted’ hacker, has passed away]]></title><description type="html"><![CDATA[<p>凯文·米特尼克（Kevin Mitnick）曾是世界上最受通缉的计算机黑客之一，于 7 月 16 日<a data-i13n="cpos:1;pos:1" href="https://www.nytimes.com/2023/07/20/technology/kevin-mitnick-dead-hacker.html">去世</a>，享年 59 岁。根据他的<a data-i13n="cpos:2;pos:1" href="https://www.dignitymemorial.com/obituaries/las-vegas-nv/kevin-mitnick-11371668">讣告</a>，米特尼克与胰腺癌抗争了一年多，目前正在匹兹堡大学医学中心接受治疗。他的讣告写道：“他一生的大部分内容读起来就像一个小说故事。”这也许是描述他的故事的完美方式。米特尼克第一次渗透计算机系统早在 1979 年，但直到 1988 年他才因复制公司软件而被定罪并被判处 12 个月监禁。</p><p>他在被监管释放期间侵入了 Pacific Bell 的语音邮件计算机，然后在 90 年代作为逃犯继续侵入手机网络以及公司和政府网站。米特尼克还参与盗窃了数千份文件和信用卡号码，但他的讣告称他“从未从任何‘受害者’那里拿过一毛钱。”他最终于 1995 年被捕，并被指控非法使用电话接入设备和计算机欺诈。显然，当局认为他当时可以获得价值数百万美元的公司商业机密。</p><span id="end-legacy-contents"></span><p>米特尼克在监狱里度过了五年，他被释放时将其描述为“假期”。从那时起，他改变了自己的职业生涯，选择成为一名白帽黑客和网络安全顾问。 2011 年，他成为 KnowBe4 的股东兼首席黑客官，该公司为客户提供安全意识培训和模拟网络钓鱼平台。在这一切发生之前，米特尼克在 12 岁时就想出了如何利用洛杉矶的公共交通系统，通过记住公交车时刻表和打孔卡，然后获得自己的打孔工具系统，这样他就可以整天乘坐公交车。米特尼克身后留下了他的妻子金伯利·米特尼克和他们未出生的孩子。</p>本文最初发表在 Engadget 上：https://www.engadget.com/kevin-mitnick-forming-the-worlds-most-wanted-hacker-has-passed-away-084912966.html?src=rss]]>; </description><link/><![CDATA[https://www.engadget.com/kevin-mitnick-formerly-the-worlds-most-wanted-hacker-has-passed-away-084912966.html?src=rss]]><source_id> engadget_479</source_id><guid ispermalink="false"> 6e7457ea-db3b-4dfc-a​​c2c-5a77e45e4a49</guid><dc:creator>玛丽埃拉·穆恩</dc:creator><source/><![CDATA[Engadget]]><dc:publisher>恩杰特</dc:publisher><dc:rightsholder>恩杰特</dc:rightsholder><pubDate>Thu, 20 Jul 2023 08:49:12 +0000</pubDate><ingested> 1689853649</ingested><modified> 2023-07-20T11:47:32+00:00 </modified><category><![CDATA[Information Technology]]></category><category><![CDATA[Society & Culture]]></category><category><![CDATA[Crime & Justice]]></category><category><![CDATA[site|engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[provider_name|Engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[region|US]]></category><category><![CDATA[language|en-US]]></category><category><![CDATA[author_name|Mariella Moon]]></category><media:content height="2667" medium="image" url="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-07/116f9da0-26f3-11ee-aff7-724b3b2cc231" width="4000"><media:keywords>标题</media:keywords><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[1]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[ ]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[ ]]></media:description><media:title><![CDATA[ ]]></media:title></media:content><media:content height="2667" medium="image" url="https://media-mbst-pub-ue1.s3.amazonaws.com/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-07/116f9da0-26f3-11ee-aff7-724b3b2cc231" width="4000"><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[2]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[John Leyba/The Denver Post via Getty Images]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[DENVER, CO - MARCH 13: Kevin Mitnick was in Denver to give a presentation to BBVA Compass bank clients on March 13, 2018 at the Halcyon Hotel in Denver Colorado.  Kevin Mitnick made headlines in 1995 when he was arrested by the FBI for hacking computers. He really put a face on this new cybersecurity threat even though what he was caught doing at the time seems not very nefarious (hacking voice mail systems, snooping around corporate networks). He's apparently changed his ways and runs his own company. Clients hire him to break into their own computer networks to see how secure they really are.]]></media:description><media:title><![CDATA[931646430 - Kevin Mitnick - hacker / cybersecurity]]></media:title></media:content></item><item><title><![CDATA[Google is reportedly testing an AI tool that can generate news articles]]></title><description type="html"><![CDATA[<p>据<a data-i13n="cpos:1;pos:1" href="https://www.nytimes.com/2023/07/19/business/google-artificial-intelligence-news-articles.html"><em>《纽约时报》</em></a>报道，谷歌正在测试一项代号为“Genesis”的新人工智能技术，该技术可以生成新闻文章。据报道，这家科技巨头不仅向<em>《泰晤士报》</em>展示了该工具，还向<em>《华盛顿邮报》</em>和拥有<em>《华尔街日报》</em>的新闻集团的高管展示了该工具。根据现场见证者的报告，Genesis 可以从输入的数据中提取副本，无论是时事还是其他类型的信息。显然，谷歌认为记者可以将其用作某种助手来自动执行任务，并让他们腾出时间去做其他事情。</p><p>一些目睹示威活动的人称其“令人不安”。他们还表示，这似乎忽视了撰写准确、易于理解的作品所需的工作。纽约城市大学新闻学教授杰夫·贾维斯 (Jeff Jarvis) 告诉<em>《泰晤士报</em>》，“如果这项技术能够可靠地传递事实信息”，记者就应该使用该工具。由于谷歌尚未推出 Genesis，我们无法判断它是否真的可以，或者是否很容易导致错误信息的传播。正如<em>《泰晤士报》</em>指出的那样，谷歌一直在快速部署人工智能技术，以追赶微软支持的公司 OpenAI。其生成式人工智能技术 Bard 在 Twitter 上首次亮相后就被<a data-i13n="cpos:2;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/google-bard-chatbot-false-information-twitter-ad-165533095.html">发现散布错误信息</a>。</p><span id="end-legacy-contents"></span><p>一些出版物最近尝试使用人工智能工具，但结果并不理想。 <em>CNET</em>在发现其以 CNET Money 署名发表的 77 篇机器撰写文章中的大部分存在重大错误后， <a data-i13n="cpos:3;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/cnet-corrected-41-of-its-77-ai-written-articles-201519489.html">不得不进行更正</a>。就在本月早些时候， <em>Gizmodo 的 io9</em> <a data-i13n="cpos:4;pos:1" href="https://variety.com/2023/digital/news/io9-ai-generated-star-wars-article-errors-1235662194/">发表了</a>一篇《星球大战》文章，其中充满了归因于“Gizmodo 机器人”的错误。 <em>io9</em>副主编 James Whitbrook<a data-i13n="cpos:5;pos:1" href="https://twitter.com/Jwhitbrook/status/1676703614872502273">表示，</a>该网站的编辑团队没有参与其发布，因此在发布之前没有机会对其进行编辑更正。</p>本文最初发表在 Engadget 上，网址为 https://www.engadget.com/google-is-reportedly-testing-an-ai-tool-that-c​​an-generate-news-articles-054602544.html?src=rss]]>; </description><link/><![CDATA[https://www.engadget.com/google-is-reportedly-testing-an-ai-tool-that-can-generate-news-articles-054602544.html?src=rss]]><source_id> engadget_479</source_id><guid ispermalink="false"> b2d3affc-6ab6-428c-bdf6-6172a719fb53</guid><dc:creator>玛丽埃拉·穆恩</dc:creator><source/><![CDATA[Engadget]]><dc:publisher>恩杰特</dc:publisher><dc:rightsholder>恩杰特</dc:rightsholder><pubDate>Thu, 20 Jul 2023 05:46:02 +0000</pubDate><ingested> 1689831957</ingested><modified> 2023-07-20T05:46:02+00:00 </modified><category><![CDATA[site|engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[provider_name|Engadget]]></category><category><![CDATA[region|US]]></category><category><![CDATA[language|en-US]]></category><category><![CDATA[author_name|Mariella Moon]]></category><media:content height="4213" medium="image" url="https://s.yimg.com/os/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-07/f2a5e070-26b4-11ee-bffb-655df49b92b8" width="6320"><media:keywords>标题</media:keywords><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[1]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[ ]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[ ]]></media:description><media:title><![CDATA[ ]]></media:title></media:content><media:content height="4213" medium="image" url="https://media-mbst-pub-ue1.s3.amazonaws.com/creatr-uploaded-images/2023-07/f2a5e070-26b4-11ee-bffb-655df49b92b8" width="6320"><media:media_html><![CDATA[ ]]></media:media_html><dc:identifier><![CDATA[2]]></dc:identifier><media:credit><![CDATA[400tmax via Getty Images]]></media:credit><media:description><![CDATA[Seattle, USA - Jun 17, 2023: People passing the Fremont neighborhood Google building late in the day.]]></media:description><media:title><![CDATA[Fremont Tech]]></media:title></media:content></item><item><title><![CDATA[Microsoft will deliver improved HoloLens combat goggles to Army testers this month]]></title><description type="html"><![CDATA[<p>微软再次与美国军方测试其基于 HoloLens 的<a data-i13n="cpos:1;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/2018-11-29-us-army-480-million-microsoft-hololens-contract.html">战斗护目镜</a>。该公司已向 Engadget 证实，将在 7 月底之前向陆军提供改进的 IVAS（集成视觉增强系统）1.2 设备。微软表示，这些更新的增强现实模型比以前“更薄、更轻、更平衡”。反过来，这应该会让他们更加舒适并提高士兵的表现。</p><p>陆军<a data-i13n="cpos:2;pos:1" href="https://www.bloomberg.com/news/articles/2023-07-19/microsoft-is-on-track-to-deliver-improved-goggles-us-army-says?sref=10lNAhZ9">告诉</a><em>彭博社，</em>两个小队将在 8 月底测试 20 个 IVAS 护目镜原型。他们将评估弱光功能、可靠性以及是否<a data-i13n="cpos:3;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/microsoft-hololens-fails-us-army-tests-135010970.html">会让士兵感到不适</a>。去年，一些测试者抱怨恶心、头痛和眼睛疲劳，而另一些测试者则对体积大、视野窄以及在夜间可能暴露士兵存在的显示屏发光不满意。关键功能也相对频繁地出现故障。</p><span id="end-legacy-contents"></span><p> HoloLens 技术旨在<a data-i13n="cpos:4;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/2019-04-06-us-army-shows-hol">提高战场意识</a>。步兵可以看到彼此的位置，获取重要的健康统计数据并使用不太显眼的夜视仪。他们可以更好地协调攻击，并在出现受伤或疲劳迹象时发出警告。如果八月份的测试成功，该技术可能会在几年内投入使用。陆军将在 2024 年 7 月至 9 月之间授予第二次实地研究合同，最早可能在 2025 年 4 月进行作战测试。陆军可以在几个月后部署 IVAS。</p><p>然而，这项测试的影响很大。虽然陆军在十年内可能花费高达 219 亿美元购买多达 121,000 个 IVAS 装置，但在收到问题报告后， <a data-i13n="cpos:5;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/microsoft-hololens-army-combat-goggles-congress-block-202637552.html">国会于 1 月份阻止了早期护目镜的进一步订购</a>。相反，政客们向微软提供了 4000 万美元来改造硬件。如果仍然存在问题，陆军可以取消该计划。这不仅会让微软失去一份利润丰厚的合同，还会使人们对 HoloLens 本身产生进一步的怀疑。该团队去年因不当行为指控而<a data-i13n="cpos:6;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/hololens-chief-alex-kipman-leaving-microsoft-053826614.html">失去了首席开发人员 Alex Kipman</a> ，<a data-i13n="cpos:7;pos:1" href="https://www.engadget.com/big-tech-layoffs-2023-152856197.html">今年年初的裁员</a>对混合现实部门造成了严重打击。</p>本文最初发表在 Engadget 上：https://www.engadget.com/microsoft-will-deliver-improved-hololens-combat-goggles-to-army-testers-this-month-211521914.html?src=rss]]>; </description><link/><![CDATA[https://www.engadget.com/microsoft-will-deliver-improved-hololens-combat-goggles-to-army-testers-this-month-211521914.html?src=rss]]><source_id> engadget_479</source_id><guid ispermalink="false"> 0138d172-67fb-4241-a596-239f7ad575cb</guid><dc:creator>乔恩·芬加斯</dc:creator><source/><![CDATA[Engadget]]><dc:publi